{
  "texts": [
    "Problems and challengesMany traceability problems are people-related.",
    "This was already recognized during early research and still is an area with great research potential today [33,61,101].",
    "The most frequently mentioned people-related problem is to satisfy all involved roles, their interests, and their knowledge [36,.",
    "Often the benefits are not known to all people involved or the effort and benefits belong to different roles.",
    "This kind of distribution appears, for example, between providers and end users."
  ]
}